  <h3>1. Why FAQ Schema Is a Voice Search Superpower</h3>
  <p>Schema markup (also called structured data) is code that you add to your HTML to help search engines understand the meaning of your content. For voice search, <strong>FAQ schema</strong> is the most powerful type because it explicitly tells Google: “This is a question, and this is its answer.”</p>
  <p>When Google sees FAQ schema, it can:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Display your question and answer as a <strong>rich result</strong> (the expandable boxes you see in search).</li>
    <li>Read your answer aloud in voice search results (if you have the best/most concise answer).</li>
    <li>Pull your answer into a <strong>featured snippet</strong> (position zero), which is often what Google Assistant reads.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>In Kenya, where Google’s featured snippets are less competitive than in the US or UK, adding FAQ schema gives you a massive advantage. We have seen local businesses rank for voice queries within <strong>7–14 days</strong> of implementing FAQ schema – no backlinks, no domain authority required.</p>

  <h3>2. Step‑by‑Step: How to Create a Voice‑Optimized FAQ Page (Kenya Focus)</h3>
  <p>Follow these steps exactly. You do not need a developer – we will give you the HTML code.</p>

  <h4>Step 1: Brainstorm 30–50 Voice Questions (Use Section 4 Keywords)</h4>
  <p>Take the conversational keywords you found in Section 4. Convert each keyword into a full question. Example:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Keyword: “best nyama choma near Westlands” → Question: “Where can I find the best nyama choma restaurant in Westlands, Nairobi?”</li>
