  <h4>Step 2: Write Concise, Voice‑Ready Answers (40–60 Words)</h4>
  <p>Voice answers must be <strong>short, direct, and conversational</strong>. Aim for 40–60 words – long enough to be helpful, short enough for Google to read aloud in 10–15 seconds.</p>
  <p><strong>Bad answer (too long, complex):</strong> “Our company, which was founded in 2018 and has over 50 employees, provides a wide range of digital marketing services including SEO, social media management, content creation, and web design. We are located in Westlands and you can call us at 0712345678.”</p>
  <p><strong>Good answer (concise):</strong> “DK Digital SEO provides affordable SEO services in Nairobi. We help small businesses rank on Google and get more calls. Call 0710346425 for a free quote.”</p>
  <p><strong>Even better (includes target keyword naturally):</strong> “For affordable SEO services in Kenya, contact DK Digital SEO. We are based in Nairobi and offer voice search optimization, local SEO, and technical audits. Call or WhatsApp 0710346425 today.”</p>
  <p>Notice the good answers: under 50 words, include the keyword, end with a clear action (call).</p>

  <h4>Step 3: Group Questions into Logical Categories</h4>
  <p>Do not dump 50 questions randomly. Organize them under headings like:</p>
  <ul>
