  <p>Google Assistant can read these steps aloud one by one. If you offer a service that involves procedures (e.g., “how to apply for a loan”, “how to prepare for an SEO audit”), HowTo schema is a powerful addition.</p>
  
  <h3>9. Common Featured Snippet Mistakes (That Kill Voice Search Eligibility)</h3>
  
  <p><strong>❌ Mistake 1: Answering “yes” or “no” without context.</strong><br>
  Google needs a substantive answer. “Yes, we do” is not enough. Provide the reasoning or next steps.</p>
  
  <p><strong>❌ Mistake 2: Using the same question multiple times on the same page.</strong><br>
  This confuses Google. Each question should appear once.</p>
  
  <p><strong>❌ Mistake 3: Putting the answer in an image instead of text.</strong><br>
  Google cannot read text inside images for snippets. Always use HTML text.</p>
  
  <p><strong>❌ Mistake 4: Forgetting to update outdated answers.</strong><br>
  If your snippet answers a question with 2024 pricing but it is now 2026, Google may drop you. Review snippet‑winning pages quarterly.</p>
  
  <p><strong>❌ Mistake 5: Adding too many ads or popups above the answer.</strong><br>
  Google may decide that the user experience is poor and choose a different snippet source. Keep the area above the fold clean.</p>

