  <h3>7. Combining Multiple Schema Types on One Page (Valid and Powerful)</h3>
  <p>One page can (and should) have multiple schema types. For example, a product page could have <strong>Product, Review, Offer, and Organization</strong> schemas. An event page could have <strong>Event, Location, and Organizer</strong>. A blog post (like this one) can have <strong>BlogPosting, FAQPage, LocalBusiness, and Person (author)</strong>.</p>
  
  <p>To combine, simply create separate `<script type="application/ld+json">` blocks for each schema type. Or merge them into one block using `@graph` (advanced). The safe method: separate blocks. Example for this page:</p>
