  <strong>Problem:</strong> Hosted on a US shared server. TTFB averaged 680ms. LCP was 4.2 seconds. Voice search visibility was zero.<br>
  <strong>Solution:</strong> Moved to Truehost Kenya (local server). Enabled Brotli and HTTP/2. Added Cloudflare CDN as an extra layer.<br>
  <strong>Results (30 days):</strong> TTFB dropped to 95ms. LCP improved to 1.8s. Google PageSpeed mobile score went from 32 to 91. Voice search impressions for “houses for sale in Kilimani” and “rental apartments near me” increased by 320%. Monthly voice‑driven inquiries went from 3 to 22.</p>

  <h3>6. Advanced Technique #5: Lazy Loading Beyond Images (Iframes, Videos, Scripts)</h3>
  <p>You already add `loading="lazy"` to images. Extend to iframes (YouTube embeds) and third‑party scripts (chat widgets, analytics).</p>
  
  <h4>6.1 Lazy Loading Iframes</h4>
  <pre style="background: #1e293b; color: #e2e8f0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 0.8rem;">
&lt;iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/abc123" loading="lazy"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;
  </pre>
  
  <h4>6.2 Deferring Third‑Party Scripts</h4>
  <p>Move non‑critical scripts (chat widgets, remarketing pixels) to load after user interaction or after page load. Example using `setTimeout`:</p>
  <pre style="background: #1e293b; color: #e2e8f0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 0.8rem;">
&lt;script&gt;
  setTimeout(function() {
    var script = document.createElement('script');
    script.src = 'https://your-chat-widget.js';
    document.body.appendChild(script);
  }, 3000);
&lt;/script&gt;
  </pre>
  
  <p>Voice search users rarely interact with chat widgets immediately. Deferring them does not harm UX but significantly improves speed metrics.</p>

  <h3>7. Advanced Technique #6: Eliminate Render‑Blocking Resources (Beyond CSS)</h3>
  <p>Use <strong>Google PageSpeed Insights</strong> → “Diagnostics” → “Eliminate render‑blocking resources”. It lists specific scripts and stylesheets. Fixes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Add `defer` or `async` to `<script>` tags that are not needed for above‑the‑fold.</li>
    <li>Inline small CSS (under 10KB) instead of external files.</li>
    <li>Split CSS into critical (inline) and non‑critical (load later).</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>8. Advanced Technique #7: Optimize Web Font Loading (No Invisible Text)</h3>
  <p>You already added `&display=swap` to your Google Fonts link. But for even faster FCP, preload the font files and use `font-display: optional` for non‑critical fonts.</p>
  
  <pre style="background: #1e293b; color: #e2e8f0; padding: 15px; border-radius: 12px; overflow-x: auto; font-size: 0.8rem;">
&lt;link rel="preload" href="/fonts/inter-latin-400.woff2" as="font" type="font/woff2" crossorigin&gt;
&lt;style&gt;
  @font-face {
    font-family: 'Inter';
    src: url('/fonts/inter-latin-400.woff2') format('woff2');
    font-display: swap;
  }
&lt;/style&gt;
  </pre>
  
  <p>For non‑critical text (e.g., footer, less visible headings), use `font-display: optional` to avoid FOIT (Flash of Invisible Text) but also not delay FCP.</p>

