  <h2 style="border-left: 5px solid #f39c12; padding-left: 20px;">📈 Tracking & Analyzing Voice Search Performance – Measure the Unmeasurable</h2>
  
  <p>You have optimized conversational keywords, implemented schema, sped up your mobile site, and dominated local “near me” queries. Now, <strong>how do you know it is working?</strong> Unlike typed search, voice search does not have a dedicated “voice” filter in Google Analytics or Search Console. You cannot see a neat report saying “50 voice visits this week”. Instead, you must use a combination of indirect signals, custom tracking, and attribution techniques.</p>
  
  <p>In this section, we will show you exactly how to <strong>measure voice search ROI</strong> using free and low‑cost tools. You will learn to identify voice traffic patterns, track phone calls from voice queries, measure featured snippet wins, and calculate the incremental business value. By the end, you will have a dashboard (even a simple spreadsheet) that tells you whether your voice SEO investment is paying off.</p>

