  <h3>1. Google Search Console Hacks for Voice Search Data</h3>
  <p>Search Console does not label voice queries directly, but you can filter for queries that are <strong>highly likely to be voice</strong>. Voice queries are:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Longer (4+ words).</li>
    <li>Contain question words (who, what, where, when, why, how, can, does, is).</li>
    <li>Include “near me” or local landmarks.</li>
    <li>Have natural phrasing (“where can I find” instead of “plumber Nairobi”).</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h4>1.1 Step‑by‑Step: Extract Likely Voice Queries from GSC</h4>
  <ol>
