    <li>Go to your GBP listing on Google Maps or Search.</li>
    <li>Click “Ask a question” (you may need to be logged into a different Google account to ask as a customer). Or use the GBP dashboard → “Questions & answers” section.</li>
    <li>Type your question. Then answer it from your business account.</li>
    <li>Repeat for all common voice queries.</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h4>3.3 Kenyan Case Study: Q&A Section Tripled Voice‑Driven Inquiries for a Salon</h4>
  <p><strong>Client:</strong> Hair and beauty salon in Kilimani.<br>
  <strong>Action:</strong> Added 12 Q&A pairs covering pricing, services, parking, M‑Pesa acceptance, and Sunday hours.<br>
  <strong>Result:</strong> Within 45 days, GBP Q&A answers appeared in voice results for “salon near me open Sunday” and “hair braiding prices in Kilimani”. Voice calls increased from 8 to 27 per week. Customers often said, “I asked Google and it said you accept M‑Pesa and open at 9am Sunday.”</p>
  
  <h4>3.4 Monitor and Respond to Customer Questions Immediately</h4>
  <p>Google notifies you when customers ask new questions. Respond within <strong>24 hours</strong>. Unanswered questions hurt your voice trust signal. Set up email or SMS alerts for new Q&A activity.</p>

  <h3>4. GBP Messaging – Direct Voice‑to‑Chat Conversion</h3>
  <p>GBP Messaging allows customers to send you SMS‑style messages directly from your Google listing. For voice search users, clicking “Message” is a natural next step after hearing your listing read aloud. Enable this feature.</p>
  
