  <h3>6. GBP Categories – The Most Underrated Voice Search Factor</h3>
  <p>Your primary category is the single most important field in GBP for voice. If your category is too broad, you will lose to more specific competitors. Google’s voice algorithm matches the user’s query to your category first.</p>
  
  <h4>6.1 How to Choose the Right Primary Category</h4>
  <p>Think: What would a voice user say? If you run a bakery that also sells coffee, “Bakery” is better than “Cafe” if bread/pastries are your main offering. If you are a plumber who also does electrical work, “Plumber” is better than “Handyman” because voice users ask for “plumber”.</p>
  <p><strong>Research method:</strong> Search for your main voice keyword (e.g., “plumber near me”). Look at the top 3 GBP results. What category do they use? Copy that category if it fits.</p>
  
  <h4>6.2 Secondary Categories (Add Up to 9)</h4>
  <p>Add secondary categories for every service you offer. A restaurant can add “Fast food restaurant”, “Family restaurant”, “Takeout restaurant”, “Breakfast restaurant”, “Lunch restaurant”. Each secondary category opens new voice query opportunities.</p>
  
