  <p>Voice search is not just for finding information or local businesses – it is increasingly used for <strong>buying products</strong>. Called “voice commerce” or “v‑commerce”, this allows users to say, “Hey Google, buy a 6‑kg gas cylinder” or “Order a large pepperoni pizza from Domino’s”. In Kenya, voice commerce grew by <strong>187% in 2025-2026</strong> according to the <strong>Jumia Voice Commerce Report</strong>, driven by M‑Pesa integration and affordable smartphones.</p>
  
