  <p>For most Kenyan small e‑commerce stores, full voice reorder integration is still complex. Start with a simpler alternative: <strong>voice‑triggered WhatsApp order link</strong>. When a user says “Reorder gas cylinder”, your system sends a WhatsApp message with a payment link. This is lower tech but highly effective given WhatsApp's penetration in Kenya.</p>
  
  <h4>8.1 Kenyan Example: Voice Reordering via WhatsApp</h4>
  <p>A small dairy delivery service in Nairobi set up a voice action: “Hey Google, tell FreshMilk to reorder my weekly milk.” Google Assistant opened WhatsApp with a pre‑filled message: “I want to reorder my weekly milk delivery.” The business then processed the order manually. This low‑tech solution increased repeat voice orders by 180% in 3 months.</p>

